# Real-Time Integration & Auth Fix Plan

We are moving from a mock-heavy prototype to a fully functional application by implementing real authentication and live market data.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Authentication System
- **Backend ([backend/routes/auth.py](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/routes/auth.py))**: 
    - Enable database interaction in [register](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/routes/auth.py#12-28) and [login](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/routes/auth.py#29-47).
    - Implement proper password hashing and verification.
    - Return real JWT tokens.
- **Frontend ([frontend/app/login/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/frontend/app/login/page.tsx))**:
    - Add state for email and password.
    - Implement [handleSubmit](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/frontend/app/login/page.tsx#17-56) to call backend auth endpoints.
    - Store JWT in `localStorage` and redirect to dashboard on success.

### 2. Real-Time Market Data
- **Backend ([backend/services/market_services.py](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/market_services.py))**:
    - Integrate `ccxt` into [AnalysisService](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/market_services.py#9-49) to fetch live ticker and indicator data.
    - Update [SignalsService](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/market_services.py#50-108) to generate signals using the [PredictionEngine](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/ai_engine/prediction_engine.py#10-81) instead of hardcoded lists.
- **Backend ([backend/services/dashboard_service.py](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/dashboard_service.py))**:
    - Use live price data to calculate portfolio values.

### 4. Production & Branding Hardening
- **Global API URLs**:
    - Audit and replace all `http://localhost:8000` instances with `API_BASE_URL` (derived from `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`).
    - Ensure all fetch calls include the `Authorization` header with the JWT token.
### 6. Vercel Build Optimization
- **Vercel Entry Point Fix**:
    - Add a [vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/vercel.json) to the root directory to explicitly tell Vercel to use the `frontend` directory for the Next.js build. This prevents Vercel from incorrectly detecting the project as a Python FastAPI app due to the root [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/requirements.txt).
    - Ensure [next.config.mjs](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/frontend/next.config.mjs) is optimized for production paths.

### 7. Railway Migration
- **Railway Configuration**:
    - Add a [railway.json](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/railway.json) to the root directory to define the backend service.
    - Set the start command to `python -m backend.main` to ensure the `ai_engine` module is correctly resolved from the project root.
    - Configure Railway to use the existing [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/requirements.txt) for dependencies.

### 10. Database-Backed Real-Time Services
Transition from hardcoded mocks to full database-backed operations.
- **Risk Management**:
    - [NEW] Add [RiskSettings](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/models/schemas.py#70-81) table to [schemas.py](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/models/schemas.py).
    - Refactor [RiskService](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/market_services.py#109-136) to persist settings per user in the database.
- **Account Integration**:
    - Refactor [DashboardService](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/dashboard_service.py#5-118) to fetch user's encrypted API keys.
    - Use live keys with `ccxt` to retrieve real account balances and holdings.
- **Signal Persistence**:
    - Periodically save AI-generated signals to the `market_signals` table.
    - Update frontend to fetch signals from the database for historical review.

### 11. Robust Data Fallbacks (Live/Offline Resiliency)
Ensuring the UI reflects real-time data even if exchange APIs are unreachable.
- **Fail-Safe Mode**: 
    - Implement a `PseudoLive` fallback in [DashboardService](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/dashboard_service.py#5-118) and [AnalysisService](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/market_services.py#9-49). 
    - If `ccxt` fails (e.g., binance connection error/IP block), use cached or realistic static data for Demo Mode instead of returning zeros.
- **Allocation Logic**: Fix the bug in [DashboardService](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/dashboard_service.py#5-118) where percentages are calculated before the total portfolio value is finalized.
- **Connectivity Status**: Add a `last_updated` or [status](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/main.py#98-104) field to API responses so the frontend can display a "Live", "Cached", or "Service Warning" status to the user.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `git grep "localhost:8000"` to ensure zero hardcoded instances remain in the frontend.
- Verify database migrations for new [RiskSettings](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/models/schemas.py#70-81) table.

### Manual Verification
1. Login with a test account.
2. Configure Risk Settings and verify they persist after page refresh.
3. Verify that the Dashboard displays real account data (if API keys are provided) or a "Connect API" prompt.
